#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:4
msgid "Best practices for engine contributors"
msgstr "引擎贡献者的最佳实践"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:7
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:9
msgid ""
"Godot has a large amount of users who have the ability to contribute, given "
"the project itself is aimed mainly at users with the ability to do "
"programming. Despite this, not all of them have the same level of experience "
"working in large projects or in software engineering, which can lead to "
"common misunderstandings and bad practices during the process of "
"contributing code to the project."
msgstr ""
"由于项目本身主要针对具有编程能力的用户，因此Godot拥有大量具有贡献能力的用户。"
"尽管如此，并非所有人都具有相同水平的在大型项目或软件工程中的经验，这可能导致"
"在向项目贡献代码的过程中，出现常见的误解和不良做法。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:12
msgid "Language"
msgstr "语言"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:14
msgid ""
"The scope of this document is to be a list of best practices for "
"contributors to follow, as well as to creating a language they can use to "
"refer to common situations that arise in the process of submitting their "
"contributions."
msgstr ""
"本文件的范围是成为贡献者遵循的最佳实践列表，并创建一种语言，供他们用来指代在"
"提交他们的贡献的过程中出现的常见情形。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:16
msgid ""
"While some may find it useful to extend this to general software "
"development, our intention is to just restrict to situations that are most "
"common in our project."
msgstr ""
"尽管有些人可能发现将其扩展到通用软件开发很有用，但我们的意图是仅将其限制在我"
"们的项目中最常见的情形下。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:18
msgid ""
"Contributions are most of the time categorized as bug fixes, enhancements or "
"new features. To abstract this idea, we will call them *Solutions*, because "
"they always seek to solve something that can be described as a *Problem*."
msgstr ""
"贡献大部分时间被归类为错误修复（bug fixes），增强（enhancements）或新功能"
"（new features）。为了抽象化这个想法，我们将它们称为 *解决方案（Solutions）"
"*，因为它们始终寻求解决某些可以描述为一个 *问题（Problem）* 的东西。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:21
msgid "Best Practices"
msgstr "最佳实践"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:24
msgid "#1: The problem always comes first"
msgstr "#1: 问题永远是第一位"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:26
msgid ""
"Many contributors are extremely creative and just enjoy the process of "
"designing abstract data structures, creating nice user interfaces,or simply "
"love programming. Whatever the case may be, they come up with cool ideas, "
"which may not be actually solving any actual problems."
msgstr ""
"许多贡献者都非常有创造力，并且喜欢设计抽象数据结构，创建漂亮的用户界面或只是"
"喜欢编程的过程。无论情况怎样，他们都提出了很酷的想法，这些想法可能实际上并不"
"能解决任何实际问题。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:30
msgid ""
"These are usually called *Solutions in search of a problem*. In an ideal "
"world, they would not be harmful but, in reality, code takes time to write, "
"takes space as source and binary and requires maintenance once it exists. "
"Avoiding the addition of anything unnecessary is always considered a good "
"practice in software development."
msgstr ""
"这些通常称为 *寻找问题的解决方案（Solutions in search of a problem）*。在理想"
"的情况下，它们并不会有害，但是实际上，代码需要花费一些时间来编写，并且一旦作"
"为源代码和二进制文件存在，就需要占用空间和维护。在软件开发中，避免添加不必要"
"的东西始终被认为是一种好习惯。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:33
msgid "#2: The problem has to exist"
msgstr "#2: 问题必须存在"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:35
msgid ""
"This is a variation of the previous practice. I believe most developers "
"agree that adding anything unnecessary is not a good idea, but what "
"constitutes what is necessary and what isn't?"
msgstr ""
"这是之前做法的一种变体。我相信大多数开发人员都同意，添加任何非必需的东西不是"
"一个好主意，但是什么构成了必需，什么没有构成呢？"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:39
msgid ""
"The answer to this question is that the problem needs to *exist*. It must "
"not be speculation or a belief. The user must be using the software as "
"intended to create something they *need*. In this process, the user may "
"stumble into a problem that requires a solution in order to continue, or in "
"order to achieve greater productivity. In this case, *a solution is needed*."
msgstr ""
"这个问题的答案是该问题需要 *存在*。一定不是猜测或信念。用户必须按预期使用软件"
"来创建他们 *需要* 的东西。在这个过程中，为了继续，或为了实现更高的工作效率，"
"用户可能偶遇需要解决方案的问题。在这种情况下，*需要一种解决方案*。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:41
msgid ""
"Believing that problems may arise in the future and that the software needs "
"to be ready to solve them by the time they appear is called *\"Future "
"proofing\"* and its characterized by lines of thought such as:"
msgstr ""
"认为将来可能会出现问题，并且该软件需要在问题出现时，就已准备好解决这些问题，"
"这称为 *“未来证明”*，其特点是思路如下："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:43
msgid "I think it would be useful for users to..."
msgstr "我认为这对用户有用..."

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:44
msgid "I think users will eventually need to..."
msgstr "我认为用户最终将需要..."

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:46
msgid ""
"This is generally considered a bad habit, because trying to solve problems "
"that *don't actually exist* in the present will very often lead to code that "
"will be written but never used, or to code that is considerably more complex "
"to use and maintain than it needs to be."
msgstr ""
"这通常被认为是一种坏习惯，因为尝试解决实际 *不存在* 的问题，通常会导致将编写"
"但从未使用过的代码，或者使用和维护起来比实际需要的更加复杂的代码。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:49
msgid "#3: The problem has to be complex or frequent"
msgstr "#3: 问题必须复杂或频繁"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:51
msgid ""
"Software is designed to solve problems, but we can't expect it to solve "
"*every problem that exists under the sun*. As a game engine, Godot will "
"solve problems for you, so it helps you to make games better and faster, but "
"it won't make the *entire game* for you. A line must be drawn somewhere."
msgstr ""
"软件旨在解决问题，但我们不能指望它能够解决 *阳光下存在的每个问题*。作为游戏引"
"擎，Godot可以为您解决问题，因此可以帮助您更快更好地开发游戏，但不会为您打造 *"
"整个游戏*。必须划清界限。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:55
msgid ""
"Whether a problem is worth solving is determined by the difficulty the user "
"has to work around it. This difficulty can be expressed as:"
msgstr ""
"一个问题是否值得解决取决于用户必须解决该问题的难度。这种困难可以表示为："

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:57
msgid "The complexity of the problem"
msgstr "问题的复杂性"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:58
msgid "The frequency the problem"
msgstr "问题的频率"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:60
msgid ""
"If the problem is *too complex* for most users to solve, the software must "
"offer a ready made solution for it. Likewise, if the problem is easy for the "
"user to workaround, offering such a solution is unnecessary and it's up to "
"the user to do it."
msgstr ""
"如果问题对于大多数用户而言 *太复杂* 而无法解决，则该软件必须为其提供现成的解"
"决方案。同样，如果用户很容易解决问题，则不必提供这样的解决方案，这取决于用"
"户。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:62
msgid ""
"The exception, however, is when the user stumbles into this problem "
"*frequently enough* that having to do the simple solution every time becomes "
"an annoyance. In this case, the software must offer a solution to simplify "
"this use case."
msgstr ""
"但是，唯一的例外是，当用户偶遇该问题足够频繁时，每次必须执行简单的解决方案就"
"很烦人。在这种情况下，软件必须提供解决方案以简化此用例。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:64
msgid ""
"In our experience, in most cases it's usually obvious to tell when a problem "
"is complex or frequent, but cases may arise where drawing this line is "
"difficult. This is why discussing with other developers (next point) is "
"always advised."
msgstr ""
"根据我们的经验，在大多数情况下，通常很容易分辨出问题何时复杂或频繁出现，但有"
"时会出现很难划清界限的情况。这就是为什么总是建议与其他开发人员讨论（下一"
"点）。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:67
msgid "#4: The solution must be discussed with others"
msgstr "#4: 解决方案必须与他人讨论"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:69
msgid ""
"It is often the case that, when users stumble upon problems, they are only "
"immersed in their own project, so they will naturally try to solve the "
"problem from their own perspective, thinking only about their use case."
msgstr ""
"通常，当用户偶然发现问题时，他们只会沉浸在自己的项目中，因此他们自然会尝试从"
"自己的角度解决问题，只考虑他们的用例。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:71
msgid ""
"Because of this, user proposed solutions don't always contemplate other use "
"cases that developers are often aware of, so they are often biased towards "
"their own requirements."
msgstr ""
"因此，用户提出的解决方案并不总是考虑开发人员经常意识到的其他用例，因此它们常"
"常偏向于他们自己的需求。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:75
msgid ""
"For developers, the perspective is different. They may find the user's "
"problem too unique to justify a solution (instead of an user workaround), or "
"maybe they will suggest a partial (usually simpler or lower level) solution "
"that applies to a wider range of known problems, and leave the rest of the "
"solution up to the user."
msgstr ""
"对于开发人员而言，观点是不同的。他们可能会发现用户的问题太独特而无法证明解决"
"方案的合理性（而不是用户的解决方法），或者他们可能会建议适用于更广泛的已知问"
"题的部分（通常是更简单或更低级的）解决方案，而其余问题解决方案由用户决定。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:77
msgid ""
"In any case, before attempting a contribution, it is important to discuss "
"the actual problems with the other developers or contributors, so a better "
"agreement on implementation can be reached."
msgstr ""
"无论如何，在尝试做出贡献之前，与其他开发人员或贡献者讨论实际问题很重要，这样"
"才能在实施方面达成更好的共识。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:79
msgid ""
"The only exception, in this case, is when an area of code has a clear owner "
"(agreed by the other contributors), who talks to users directly and has the "
"most knowledge to implement a solution directly."
msgstr ""
"在这种情况下，唯一的例外是当代码区域中有明确的所有者（由其他贡献者同意）时，"
"该所有者直接与用户对话，并且拥有最了解直接实施解决方案的知识。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:82
msgid "#5: To each problem, its own solution"
msgstr "#5: 对于每个问题，都有自己的解决方案"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:84
msgid ""
"For programmers, it is always a most enjoyable challenge to find the most "
"optimal solutions to problems. Things, however, may go overboard sometimes "
"and programmers will try to come up with solutions that solve as many "
"problems as possible."
msgstr ""
"对于程序员而言，找到问题的最佳解决方案始终是最愉快的挑战。但是，有时候事情可"
"能会变得极端，程序员将尝试提出解决方案，以解决尽可能多的问题。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:86
msgid ""
"The situation will often take a turn for the worse when, in order to make "
"this solution appear even more fantastic and flexible, the pure speculation-"
"based problems (as described in #2) also make their appearance on stage."
msgstr ""
"当为了使该解决方案显得更加出色和灵活时，这种情况通常会变得更糟，因为纯粹基于"
"投机的问题（如第2点中所述）也出现在舞台上。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:90
msgid ""
"The main problem is that, in reality, it rarely works this way. Most of the "
"time, just writing an individual solution to each problem results in code "
"that is simpler and more maintainable."
msgstr ""
"主要问题是，实际上，这种方法很少起作用。在大多数情况下，仅针对每个问题编写单"
"独的解决方案就会使代码更简单，更可维护。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:92
msgid ""
"Additionally, solutions that target individual problems are better for the "
"users, as they find something that does exactly what they need, without "
"having to learn and remember a more complex system they will only need for "
"simple tasks."
msgstr ""
"此外，针对单独问题的解决方案对用户来说更好，因为他们找到了完全可以满足他们需"
"求的东西，而不必学习和记住一个更复杂的系统，他们只需要完成简单任务。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:94
msgid ""
"Big and flexible solutions also have an additional drawback which is that, "
"over time, they rarely are flexible enough for all users, which keep "
"requesting more functions added (and making the API and codebase more and "
"more complex)."
msgstr ""
"大型且灵活的解决方案还有一个缺点，那就是随着时间的推移，它们对于所有用户而言"
"都缺乏足够的灵活性，从而不断要求添加更多功能（并使API和代码库变得越来越复"
"杂）。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:97
msgid "#6: Cater to common use cases, leave the door open for the rare ones"
msgstr "#6: 迎合常见用例，为稀有案例敞开大门"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:99
msgid ""
"This is a continuation of the previous point, which further explains why "
"this way of thinking and designing software is preferred."
msgstr "这是先前观点的延续，进一步说明了为什么首选这种思想和设计软件的方式。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:101
msgid ""
"As mentioned before (in point #2), it is very difficult for us (as human "
"beings who design software) to actually understand all future user needs. "
"Trying to write very flexible structures that cater to many use cases at "
"once is often a mistake."
msgstr ""
"如前所述（在第2点中），对于我们（作为设计软件的人）来说，要真正了解所有未来的"
"用户需求非常困难。尝试编写非常灵活的结构以同时满足许多用例通常是一个错误。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:103
msgid ""
"We may come up with something we believe is brilliant, but when it's "
"actually used, we will find that users will never even use half of it, or "
"that they will require features that don't quite accommodate our original "
"design, forcing us to either throw it away or make it even more complex."
msgstr ""
"我们可能会想出一些我们认为很棒的东西，但是当实际使用它时，我们会发现用户甚至"
"不会使用其中的一半，或者他们将需要的功能无法完全适应我们的原始设计，从而迫使"
"我们要么扔掉它，要么使其变得更加复杂。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:105
msgid ""
"The question is then, how to design software that gives users what *we know "
"they need*, but that is flexible enough to allow them to do *what we don't "
"know they might need* in the future?"
msgstr ""
"那么问题是，如何设计能够为用户提供 *我们知道他们需要的东西*，但又足够灵活的软"
"件，以使他们在将来能够做 *我们不知道但他们可能需要的东西*？"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:109
msgid ""
"The answer to this question is that, to ensure users still can do what they "
"want to do, we need to give them access to a *low level API* that they can "
"use to achieve what they want, even if it's more work for them because it "
"means reimplementing some of the logic that already exists."
msgstr ""
"这个问题的答案是，为了确保用户仍然可以做他们想做的事情，我们需要让他们访问一"
"个 *低级API*，他们可以使用该API来实现他们想要的事情，即使这对他们来说是更多的"
"工作，因为这意味着重新实现一些已经存在的逻辑。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:111
msgid ""
"In real-life scenarios, these use cases will be at most rare and uncommon "
"anyway, so it makes sense a custom solution needs to be written. This is why "
"it's important to still provide users the basic building blocks to do it."
msgstr ""
"在实际场景中，这些用例无论如何最稀有且少见，因此有必要编写一个自定义解决方"
"案。这就是为什么仍然要向用户提供执行这些操作的基本构建块很重要。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:114
msgid "#7: Solutions must be local"
msgstr "#7: 解决方案必须是局部的"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:116
msgid ""
"When looking for a solution to a problem, be it implementing a new feature "
"or fixing a bug, sometimes the easiest path is to add data or a new function "
"in the core layers of code."
msgstr ""
"在寻找解决方案时，无论是实施新功能还是修复错误，有时最简单的方法是在代码的核"
"心层中添加数据或新功能。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:118
msgid ""
"The main problem here is, adding something to the core layers that will only "
"be used from a single location far away will not only make the code more "
"difficult to follow (split in two), but also make the core API larger, more "
"complex, more difficult to understand in general."
msgstr ""
"这样做的主要问题是，在核心层中添加仅在远处才能使用的内容，不仅使代码难以遵循"
"（分为两部分），而且通常会使核心API变得更大，更复杂，一般来说更难理解。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:120
msgid ""
"This is bad, because readability and cleanness of core APIs is always of "
"extreme importance given how much code relies from it, and because it's key "
"for new contributors as a starting point to learning the codebase."
msgstr ""
"这很不好，因为考虑到多少代码依赖于它，核心API的可读性和简洁性始终至关重要，并"
"且对于新贡献者而言，这是学习代码库的起点，这是关键。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:126
msgid ""
"The common reasoning for wanting to do this is that it's usually less code "
"to simply add a hack in the core layers."
msgstr ""
"对于想要做到这一点的常见理由是，它通常是更少的代码只需在核心层增加一个黑客。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:128
msgid ""
"Despite this, this practice is not advised. Generally, the code for a "
"solution should be closer to where the problem originates, even if it "
"involves more code, duplicated, more complex or is less efficient. More "
"creativity might be needed, but this path is always the advised one."
msgstr ""
"尽管如此，不建议这种做法。通常，解决方案的代码应该更接近问题的根源，即使它涉"
"及更多的代码，重复的，更复杂的或效率较低的也是如此。可能需要更多的创造力，但"
"这始终是建议之路。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:131
msgid "#8: Don't use complex canned solutions for simple problems"
msgstr "#8: 简单问题不要使用复杂罐装的解决方案"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:133
msgid ""
"Not every problem has a simple solution and, many times, the right choice is "
"to use a third party library to solve the problem."
msgstr ""
"并非每个问题都有一个简单的解决方案，很多时候，正确的选择是使用第三方库来解决"
"问题。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:135
msgid ""
"As Godot requires to be shipped in a large amount of platforms, we just "
"can't link libraries dynamically. Instead, we bundle them in our source tree."
msgstr ""
"由于Godot需要在大量平台上交付，因此我们无法动态链接库。相反，我们将它们捆绑在"
"源代码树中。"

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/community/contributing/best_practices_for_engine_contributors.rst:139
msgid ""
"As a result, we are very picky with what goes in, and we tend to prefer "
"smaller libraries (in fact, single header ones are our favorite). Only in "
"cases where there is no other choice we end up bundling something larger."
msgstr ""
"结果，我们对其中的内容非常挑剔，并且倾向于使用较小的库（实际上，单头库是我们"
"的最爱）。仅在没有其他选择的情况下，我们最终将更大的东西捆绑在一起。"
